cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.SE 

The paper proposes a neural network architecture for demand forecasting in e-retail, which involves modeling associative factors, time-series trends, and variance in demand. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and software engineering (cs.SE). However, given the focus on neural networks and deep learning, as well as the use of mixture density networks, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
